The paper discusses the problem of actively eliciting preferences from a human expert during the planning process, which is a common topic in the field of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also focuses on the interaction between the human expert and the planning framework, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (HCI), making cs.HC another likely sub-category. The use of the Hierarchical Task Network (HTN) planning framework suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of robotics (cs.RO) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper proposes an approach to improve the quality and speed of the planner, which may fall under the sub-category of swarm intelligence (cs.SI).
